summary: This is an email from a prosecutor or legal team member regarding the final major Rule 16 discovery production to Ghislaine Maxwell's defense team. It includes a cover letter and details the planned delivery of digital evidence (drives, CD, and a laptop) to defense counsel and the Metropolitan Detention Center (MDC).

persons.name: Maxwell
persons.context: The recipient of the final major Rule 16 discovery production in her criminal case.

events.title: Final Major Discovery Production to Maxwell
events.description: The prosecution plans to make what is expected to be their last big Rule 16 discovery production to Ghislaine Maxwell's defense team, including digital evidence on drives, a CD, and a laptop.

locations: 1SA (likely a reference to a legal office or courthouse location)
MDC (Metropolitan Detention Center, where Maxwell was likely held)
keyFacts: The prosecution anticipated this to be their last major Rule 16 discovery production to Ghislaine Maxwell's defense team.
The production included a chart of devices and digital evidence stored on drives, a CD, and a laptop.
Delivery was planned for November 18, 2020, with one set for defense counsel pickup at '1SA' and another to be hand-delivered to the MDC.
